# Min Stack

## Intuition
Instead of finding the minimum repeatedly, we store the minimum at each step.

## Approach
We use two stacks:
- st1 stores all elements
- st2 stores the minimum at each level

While pushing:
- Push element to st1
- Push min(val, st2.top()) to st2

While popping:
- Pop from both stacks

Top:
- Return st1.top()

GetMin:
- Return st2.top()

## Complexity
Time: O(1) for all operations  
Space: O(n)